WEBVTT

00:01.769 --> 00:03.635
<i> Dr. Cheng: We don't know how</i>
<i> you'll react to the radiation.</i>

00:03.771 --> 00:05.937
You might need someone
to take care of you.

00:05.973 --> 00:09.307
♪♪♪

00:09.309 --> 00:11.510
<i> Donovan: "explore the human</i>
<i> form",</i>

00:11.512 --> 00:13.745
And you're kirima rite?

00:14.948 --> 00:17.683
<i> Kirima: My work is more</i>
<i> sheltered, private.</i>

00:18.919 --> 00:21.386
<i> Me and my canvas.</i>
<i> My subject.</i>

00:21.455 --> 00:23.188
- What's goin' on?
You're taking off some place?

00:23.190 --> 00:26.125
- I am uh, going to see liam.

00:26.127 --> 00:29.194
<i> Gordon: Love isn't just</i>
<i> always enough.</i>

00:29.230 --> 00:31.096
- I slept with someone.

00:32.399 --> 00:33.932
I'm seeing her.
Jenny: You left.

00:34.001 --> 00:35.367
Liam: Because I'm doing
the work.

00:35.369 --> 00:37.169
- Is the work screwing
someone while you're in aa?!

00:37.304 --> 00:39.038
Your problems go way
beyond drinking.

00:39.173 --> 00:40.939
- Yeah, well, know what?
Your problem is

00:41.075 --> 00:42.674
You don't wanna be happy.
You hide behind your

00:42.676 --> 00:44.143
Sister's death, yeah.
- You're the one

00:44.145 --> 00:45.944
<i> Who's hiding out here!</i>
<i> - No, here, I'm safe.</i>

00:46.013 --> 00:47.913
- You're scared.
- No, I'm not scared. Know what?

00:48.048 --> 00:49.815
I was fine before you came here.
- So was I!

00:49.950 --> 00:51.483
- Okay! Great. All right.
(scoffs)

00:54.055 --> 00:55.453
(low hum of chatter)

00:57.224 --> 01:00.024
- Hmm. So, he's only been
here 14 days?

01:00.061 --> 01:01.693
- Fascinating, right?

01:01.829 --> 01:03.495
We found that the maggots
progressed to the thighs

01:03.630 --> 01:05.463
Much more quickly
than we thought.

01:05.499 --> 01:07.766
- Must be the humid
ontario weather.

01:08.969 --> 01:10.769
I mean, it's amazing
to have local data

01:10.771 --> 01:12.437
On decomposing bodies like this.

01:14.909 --> 01:17.409
But really,
it really is incredible.

01:17.411 --> 01:19.978
Angela: Cops, coroners,
pathologists.

01:20.114 --> 01:22.714
We'll all be able to establish
time of death more accurately,

01:22.850 --> 01:25.350
Thanks to these people
who donated their bodies.

01:26.454 --> 01:27.853
- Thank you. I mean,

01:27.855 --> 01:29.321
We're really lucky
to have all of this.

01:29.390 --> 01:31.456
- I actually had to fight
the town

01:31.492 --> 01:33.392
To let me build
this research centre.

01:33.527 --> 01:35.460
(watch beeps)
and that fight continues.

01:35.463 --> 01:37.462
I have a town council meeting
in half an hour.

01:37.598 --> 01:39.198
Stay as long as you like.

01:39.200 --> 01:41.799
My son knows this place
better than I do.

01:42.870 --> 01:44.435
- Thank you.

01:45.606 --> 01:47.606
Can--are we, can--
- yeah, of course, of course.

01:47.608 --> 01:49.141
<i> - Thank you.</i>

01:49.210 --> 01:52.144
♪♪♪

01:52.213 --> 01:54.746
(grass crunches underfoot)

01:56.016 --> 01:58.082
- So, that's your mom?

01:58.119 --> 01:59.618
- (chuckles) ha, yeah.

01:59.687 --> 02:01.553
I know, I know,
you think it's weird,

02:01.555 --> 02:04.355
<i> But it's important work.</i>

02:04.391 --> 02:06.291
And if your mother made
something this cool,

02:06.426 --> 02:08.126
You'd work with her, too.

02:08.129 --> 02:10.628
Man: Doctor garcia!
Doctor garcia!

02:12.633 --> 02:14.399
- Uh, I, I don't know.

02:14.535 --> 02:16.902
(ominous music)

02:18.973 --> 02:20.505
(water burbles)

02:21.642 --> 02:28.613
♪♪♪

02:28.649 --> 02:33.652
♪♪♪

02:33.654 --> 02:40.558
♪♪♪

02:44.064 --> 02:45.863
This isn't one of yours,
is it?

02:45.900 --> 02:47.733
- No, it's not.

02:47.868 --> 02:50.602
♪♪♪

02:50.737 --> 02:53.805
(ominous music)

02:54.875 --> 02:57.809
♪♪♪

03:01.015 --> 03:02.447
(grass crunches underfoot)

03:03.617 --> 03:05.150
- If this gets out,

03:05.152 --> 03:07.085
They'll shut my mom down.

03:07.154 --> 03:08.820
- We'll call the chief
of police.

03:08.889 --> 03:10.655
I'll tell him that my team
is investigating it.

03:10.691 --> 03:13.158
I'll ask him to keep it
confidential for the time being.

03:13.160 --> 03:14.993
- They'll do that?
- Let's hope so.

03:16.197 --> 03:18.230
The body's stained red.

03:21.502 --> 03:23.202
Did this land used
to be a peat bog?

03:23.337 --> 03:24.970
- Half the grounds were.

03:24.972 --> 03:26.772
It's the reason town council
gave us this land.

03:26.774 --> 03:28.240
- Got it.

03:29.710 --> 03:32.277
Okay, well,
let's get him outta here.

03:33.480 --> 03:35.480
(fly buzzes)

03:38.185 --> 03:40.252
(phone chimes, buzzes)

03:43.190 --> 03:44.589
(waking groan)

03:46.961 --> 03:48.460
(pencil rasps in background)

03:52.399 --> 03:54.299
- Can I see it?

04:00.541 --> 04:02.674
(chuckles lightly)

04:07.481 --> 04:09.414
- You don't have to tell me
about those marks on your back,

04:09.416 --> 04:11.082
If you don't want to.

04:12.686 --> 04:15.853
- It's from a treatment
I'm having. Radiation.

04:17.024 --> 04:18.556
It's a side effect.

04:20.527 --> 04:22.894
- You have cancer.
- Yeah.

04:22.930 --> 04:25.430
A solitary spinal plasmacytoma.

04:26.900 --> 04:28.967
It's a tumour on my spine.

04:28.969 --> 04:31.470
But I, I'm dealing with it.

04:31.605 --> 04:33.738
- Does it hurt?
- No.

04:36.010 --> 04:37.376
- Are you scared?

04:43.517 --> 04:45.116
- Yeah.

04:45.152 --> 04:47.853
- Well, I think it makes you
more beautiful.

04:47.988 --> 04:50.522
- (chuckles)
- what's it called again? Sol--

04:50.524 --> 04:53.792
- Solitary spinal plasmacytoma.

04:53.861 --> 04:57.496
- Solitary.
You have a lonely cancer.

04:57.498 --> 04:59.597
- Yeah. (chuckles)

04:59.633 --> 05:01.400
(both laugh)

05:02.636 --> 05:04.403
(phone chimes, buzzes)
- ah... Hmm.

05:04.538 --> 05:06.671
- I'm gonna have to take that
away from you.

05:06.674 --> 05:09.474
- Really?
Well, come and get it.

05:09.476 --> 05:11.142
- Yeah.
- Come and get it.

05:11.211 --> 05:12.744
(chuckling)

05:12.879 --> 05:14.412
Jenny: Hello?
- Ugh!

05:14.481 --> 05:16.214
Jenny: Hello?

05:17.418 --> 05:19.084
- (sighs)

05:19.086 --> 05:20.819
- Hey, donovan.
- Yes?

05:20.821 --> 05:22.487
- You're not gonna believe this.

05:22.489 --> 05:25.891
<i> Donovan: A Halloween mask?</i>
<i> That's a new one.</i>

05:25.893 --> 05:27.559
- Bogs have low ph level,

05:27.628 --> 05:29.561
So, it's like he's been pickled.

05:29.563 --> 05:31.963
- I'm gonna miss pickles.

05:32.099 --> 05:33.464
(jenny chuckles)
dennis: Doctor cooper!

05:34.768 --> 05:36.435
- Oh, uh yeah,
so I'll send the body to uh,

05:36.437 --> 05:40.005
To toronto for the autopsy
with the help of doctor garcia.

05:40.007 --> 05:42.107
- Dennis. Call me dennis.
- Yeah.

05:43.444 --> 05:45.110
- Okay.

05:45.112 --> 05:48.180
You know, I always wanted
to be a surgeon,

05:48.182 --> 05:49.981
Not a pathologist,

05:50.050 --> 05:52.517
But my hand wasn't steady
enough because of this.

05:53.587 --> 05:55.253
The dead are more forgiving,

05:55.322 --> 05:57.555
But that means I get
to work with my mom.

05:57.557 --> 05:59.724
- Uh, his mother, angela,
runs the place.

06:00.794 --> 06:02.427
- Okay, here we go.

06:04.932 --> 06:06.664
Time for the big reveal.

06:06.700 --> 06:10.067
♪♪♪

06:11.605 --> 06:14.473
Blunt force trauma
to the nasal spine,

06:14.475 --> 06:16.874
Maxilla, and zygomatic bones.
- Mm-hmm, yeah,

06:16.910 --> 06:19.277
It looks like he was struck
with a lot of force.

06:19.346 --> 06:21.680
- And he's wearing a hot pink
anarchy earring.

06:21.815 --> 06:23.382
<i> Angela: A what?</i>

06:23.517 --> 06:25.750
<i> (flies buzzing)</i>

06:26.887 --> 06:28.553
- Ma, you okay?

06:30.657 --> 06:32.824
- You know him.

06:32.826 --> 06:34.759
- It's andy nyland.

06:34.762 --> 06:36.494
- Who's andy nyland?

06:37.631 --> 06:39.431
- We went to school together,

06:39.566 --> 06:42.700
But he vanished without
a trace when I was 16.

06:42.702 --> 06:44.736
(ominous music)

06:47.574 --> 06:49.540
(clock ticks)

06:56.049 --> 06:57.649
- You sure it's my brother?

07:00.287 --> 07:03.788
- We have to do a dna test
to make sure,

07:03.791 --> 07:06.791
But we got a visual id
from doctor garcia.

07:09.530 --> 07:12.230
- Angela?

07:12.266 --> 07:14.132
- She was there
when we found the body.

07:15.736 --> 07:17.268
- I see.

07:17.337 --> 07:19.270
Uh, could,
could I ask you please

07:19.306 --> 07:22.340
Not to tell my father
you found andy?

07:22.476 --> 07:24.276
<i> He couldn't handle it.</i>

07:24.278 --> 07:26.410
(footsteps tap lightly)

07:26.447 --> 07:28.179
- Thanks again!
- See ya later!

07:29.483 --> 07:31.282
- Good, goodbye!
(door shuts)

07:31.318 --> 07:33.150
- Your father had a stroke.

07:33.187 --> 07:35.119
- Doctor called it broca's
aphasia.

07:35.189 --> 07:37.121
- Means the cognition is intact,

07:37.157 --> 07:39.624
But the speech is impaired.
(sympathetic exhale)

07:41.562 --> 07:43.795
I'm really sorry.

07:45.799 --> 07:47.832
- Cops gave him that stroke.

07:47.835 --> 07:50.001
- He was questioned
after andy disappeared.

07:50.037 --> 07:51.470
- Oh, yeah.

07:51.605 --> 07:53.771
Single dad, atheist,
bit of a drinker.

07:53.907 --> 07:56.040
<i> In a small religious town</i>
<i> in the 80s.</i>

07:56.109 --> 07:58.209
He might as well
have been dahmer.

07:59.379 --> 08:01.913
They dragged his name
through the mud.

08:01.915 --> 08:03.948
Few months later,
he had a stroke.

08:04.985 --> 08:07.252
- Were any charges ever laid?
- No!

08:07.321 --> 08:09.120
When the cops couldn't
find andy's body,

08:09.189 --> 08:11.022
They decided he was a runaway.

08:12.059 --> 08:13.891
They closed the case.

08:14.928 --> 08:16.928
I really wanted to believe them.

08:20.400 --> 08:22.233
Which is why I did
this crazy thing.

08:25.506 --> 08:27.872
<i> I know we use our home</i>
<i> as a b&b</i>

08:27.941 --> 08:29.674
And we could use the space,

08:29.710 --> 08:32.243
But we felt like,
if we boxed it all up,

08:33.547 --> 08:35.614
Andy would never come home.

08:35.616 --> 08:39.551
♪♪♪

08:39.686 --> 08:42.354
(rock music plays)

08:42.356 --> 08:49.294
♪♪♪

08:49.363 --> 08:55.300
♪♪♪

08:55.369 --> 08:57.168
- The cops never touched
any of this.

08:57.170 --> 08:59.771
- No. Dumber than a pile
of rocks, those boys.

09:01.642 --> 09:03.507
- Man, do I need a drink.

09:06.547 --> 09:09.113
- Well, let's go back in time.

09:09.182 --> 09:10.582
- (small chuckle)

09:10.651 --> 09:12.383
♪♪♪

09:16.723 --> 09:18.523
(pages flip)

09:21.261 --> 09:26.865
♪♪♪

09:28.402 --> 09:29.734
- Check out the hair.

09:29.770 --> 09:31.669
- (laughs)

09:32.739 --> 09:36.408
Picture me in a flattop,
only twice as high.

09:36.543 --> 09:38.276
- Thanks for that visual.

09:38.278 --> 09:39.877
(both laugh)

09:41.848 --> 09:43.481
(drawer rattles)

09:43.550 --> 09:45.550
- Didn't roxanna say her dad
reported andy missing

09:45.685 --> 09:47.685
In November?
- Yeah. Why?

09:47.721 --> 09:49.287
This is his agenda,

09:49.422 --> 09:52.289
And every page after
October 5th is blank.

09:54.394 --> 09:56.360
I'm gonna step outside.

09:56.396 --> 09:58.062
Make a call.
- Okay.

09:59.733 --> 10:01.433
(papers rustle)

10:04.071 --> 10:10.041
♪♪♪

10:10.077 --> 10:16.982
♪♪♪

10:19.453 --> 10:21.386
<i>(young helen reads) "dear andy,</i>
<i> I know you're cheating on me</i>

10:21.455 --> 10:23.455
<i>With another girl. I don't know</i>
<i> how you could do this to me,</i>

10:23.457 --> 10:24.922
<i> After everything</i>
<i> we've been through.</i>

10:24.958 --> 10:26.924
<i> Your actions have caused</i>
<i> so much pain and heartache."</i>

10:26.960 --> 10:28.526
<i> - Kindergarten rules apply.</i>

10:28.595 --> 10:31.529
Everything back,
right where you found it.

10:32.732 --> 10:34.799
- Of course.

10:36.236 --> 10:38.669
(footsteps thud)
- hmm.

10:41.842 --> 10:43.341
- Satan's sister.

10:43.476 --> 10:45.076
- It was andy's band.

10:45.211 --> 10:47.612
They were playing battle of the
bands the week he disappeared.

10:47.614 --> 10:49.881
They actually had a chance
at winning.

10:51.151 --> 10:53.084
<i> Andy was talented.</i>

10:53.153 --> 10:55.086
After he disappeared,

10:57.891 --> 11:00.224
I lost a lot of friends.
All my friends, really.

11:02.963 --> 11:05.296
- I'm sorry.
- No, no.

11:05.432 --> 11:06.831
Going through it on
my own showed me

11:06.966 --> 11:09.367
How strong I really am, so...
(small chuckle)

11:10.503 --> 11:13.237
I guess they did me a favour,
right.

11:14.908 --> 11:16.641
- Yeah.

11:20.380 --> 11:22.580
(receding footsteps thud)

11:22.649 --> 11:29.654
♪♪♪

11:29.656 --> 11:32.590
♪♪♪

11:32.626 --> 11:34.792
(papers rustle)

11:38.598 --> 11:40.397
- Thank you, thank you.
I appreciate it. Bye.

11:40.434 --> 11:42.300
Local ds just confirmed,

11:42.369 --> 11:44.669
Andy's dad waited a month
to report him missing.

11:44.671 --> 11:46.271
Plenty of time to hide evidence.

11:46.406 --> 11:49.607
- Blunt force trauma to the
face is a very personal injury.

11:49.676 --> 11:51.142
- Usually happens when
the victim

11:51.277 --> 11:53.177
Knows the attacker intimately.

11:53.246 --> 11:54.779
- Andy had a high school
girlfriend.

11:54.781 --> 11:57.081
Apparently, things went sour.
Her name was helen.

11:57.084 --> 11:59.584
She thought he was cheating
on her.

11:59.586 --> 12:01.552
(paper rustles)

12:01.588 --> 12:03.788
- A lock of hair?
- Yeah.

12:05.558 --> 12:07.225
- What's the body saying?

12:07.227 --> 12:09.293
You heard from your office yet?
- Let's see.

12:09.329 --> 12:10.962
(keys tap)

12:12.699 --> 12:16.568
He says, no old fractures,
scarring, or trauma.

12:16.703 --> 12:18.603
- Rules out physically
abusive dad.

12:18.672 --> 12:21.639
- Yeah. The body was found
on its back,

12:21.708 --> 12:23.508
With its hands by its side.

12:23.643 --> 12:25.309
- Which indicates
it was placed there

12:25.345 --> 12:26.978
By someone who cared about him.

12:27.047 --> 12:30.048
- Well, maybe we talk to helen.

12:32.585 --> 12:34.986
(metal rattles)
- ah!

12:35.121 --> 12:37.922
- Good.
- Son of a grouse!

12:37.924 --> 12:39.991
- I told you so, grandpa.

12:39.993 --> 12:41.559
Oh great, and
"I toldja so" too.

12:41.628 --> 12:43.261
That and a win ticket
at woodbine

12:43.263 --> 12:45.362
Might make me some money.
(sighs)

12:46.733 --> 12:49.000
- Okay, you know I never
get your references, right?

12:49.069 --> 12:50.968
- Yeah, okay.
You don't need to know.

12:51.037 --> 12:52.737
- Could you pass me
the whatchamacallit?

12:52.872 --> 12:55.206
- Let's do a trade.
- Rag.

12:55.341 --> 12:57.008
- Yep.
- White one. Thank you.

12:57.077 --> 12:59.043
- Are you okay?
That's a bit um--

12:59.179 --> 13:01.212
- No, it's just a little nick.
We're okay.

13:01.347 --> 13:02.680
- Don't like that.

13:02.716 --> 13:04.749
- You know what you could
get me though,

13:04.884 --> 13:07.484
Is from liam's toolchest,
the um, ratchet.

13:08.622 --> 13:10.087
- I will look.

13:10.123 --> 13:12.790
- The, the bent arm.
- We will see.

13:14.594 --> 13:16.761
- Just bring me the whole
toolbox, if you have to.

13:21.134 --> 13:23.167
(sighs)

13:23.203 --> 13:26.838
♪♪♪

13:26.973 --> 13:28.907
(approaching footsteps crunch)

13:31.144 --> 13:34.245
- So, you gonna get this car
runnin', or what?

13:34.281 --> 13:35.980
- You bet I am!

13:36.115 --> 13:38.049
Gonna get this car runnin'.

13:38.184 --> 13:41.085
Just hummin'.
'cause that's what I do.

13:42.422 --> 13:44.856
- Good.
- You know that.

13:44.991 --> 13:47.491
- 'cause it'd be nice to go
for a ride sometime.

13:49.395 --> 13:53.130
- Okay. It would be nice
to go for a ride.

13:53.200 --> 13:55.199
Where would you wanna go?

13:55.202 --> 13:57.534
- Hmm, I don't know.

13:57.571 --> 14:00.004
How 'bout the drive-in?

14:00.040 --> 14:01.672
- Oh.

14:01.708 --> 14:03.741
- We haven't been there
in a long while.

14:03.810 --> 14:06.544
- No, I should say not.
Okay!

14:06.679 --> 14:09.347
I'll even spring
for the buttered popcorn.

14:09.349 --> 14:11.482
- Mmm. You're on.
- (chuckles)

14:13.587 --> 14:16.053
Ross: Hey, grandpa.
- Yeah?

14:16.055 --> 14:17.822
- Is this it?
- Yeah.

14:17.824 --> 14:19.490
- 'cause I, um,
(rattling)

14:20.593 --> 14:22.727
Is this normal?
- Yeah, that's it.

14:22.796 --> 14:24.795
- Good one.

14:28.134 --> 14:29.900
(bicycle spokes click)

14:31.104 --> 14:33.271
(approaching music
plays faintly)

14:33.340 --> 14:36.874
♪♪♪

14:37.009 --> 14:39.076
<i> Neil: Hi, jenny.</i>
<i> It's doctor sharma.</i>

14:39.145 --> 14:41.312
<i> I'm sorry things didn't</i>
<i> work out with liam,</i>

14:41.381 --> 14:44.114
<i>But you put yourself out there,</i>
<i> and that's good.</i>

14:46.152 --> 14:48.252
<i> I know you're angry and hurt.</i>

14:49.722 --> 14:52.456
<i>It's okay to pause your therapy</i>
<i> but don't shut down, jenny.</i>

14:53.593 --> 14:55.860
<i> Feel those feelings.</i>
<i> I'm here if you need me.</i>

14:55.995 --> 14:57.594
(exhales, beeps call off)

14:57.631 --> 14:59.463
(80s tune plays)
♪ because of circumstance ♪

15:00.767 --> 15:02.934
♪ like it's a game of chance ♪

15:04.470 --> 15:06.937
♪ and we just don't
want to believe it ♪

15:08.408 --> 15:10.475
♪ what we need to survive ♪

15:10.610 --> 15:12.543
- She brought her own
walk-up music.

15:12.545 --> 15:13.878
(turns music off)

15:16.349 --> 15:17.948
- Helen young?

15:17.984 --> 15:21.018
- Oh, wow! Honey,
I barely got here in time.

15:22.355 --> 15:25.222
There's a dark indigo cloud
near your root chakra.

15:27.127 --> 15:28.625
- Uh, sorry.

15:28.662 --> 15:30.828
No, that's not why we called.

15:30.897 --> 15:32.630
Uh, as I said on the phone,

15:32.765 --> 15:35.800
Detective mcavoy and I
wanted to talk to you

15:35.802 --> 15:37.634
About andy nyland.

15:39.105 --> 15:41.238
- I haven't heard that name
in a long time.

15:41.308 --> 15:43.775
Uh, what about him?

15:43.777 --> 15:46.077
- We found his body
this morning.

15:46.212 --> 15:48.379
(ominous music)

15:48.514 --> 15:50.214
(emotional exhale)

15:53.620 --> 15:57.121
I, I need to put my toes
in the earth.

15:59.693 --> 16:02.326
<i> (calming exhales)</i>

16:06.433 --> 16:07.932
(dirt crunches)

16:08.067 --> 16:09.834
(calming exhales)

16:11.604 --> 16:12.937
- (sighs) poor roxy.

16:17.710 --> 16:19.677
How did andy,

16:19.812 --> 16:21.011
I mean...

16:22.281 --> 16:23.948
Did someone hurt him?

16:24.083 --> 16:25.817
- Do you know someone
who'd want to?

16:29.289 --> 16:31.588
- I knew this day would come.

16:33.059 --> 16:35.559
Here, take my hand.

16:37.430 --> 16:39.597
(ethereal music intensifies)

16:39.732 --> 16:46.637
♪♪♪

16:46.639 --> 16:49.774
(flames crackle)

16:51.311 --> 16:54.645
♪♪♪

16:54.647 --> 16:56.246
(sobbing)

16:56.282 --> 16:59.650
<i> Andy and I had a very</i>
<i> tumultuous relationship</i>

16:59.786 --> 17:01.519
<i> In that typical</i>
<i> high school way.</i>

17:01.521 --> 17:03.120
(shaky exhales)

17:03.189 --> 17:05.123
<i> Finally, I'd had enough.</i>

17:05.258 --> 17:07.191
(ominous music)

17:08.661 --> 17:10.595
<i> I found a spell in a zine,</i>

17:10.730 --> 17:13.630
<i> That promised it could erase a</i>
<i>person from your life, forever.</i>

17:16.302 --> 17:19.170
<i> I gathered all the ingredients</i>
<i> for my witch bottle -</i>

17:19.305 --> 17:22.807
<i> Fingernail clippings,</i>
<i> nails, tacks.</i>

17:26.846 --> 17:28.045
(blood drips)

17:28.180 --> 17:29.814
(rips paper violently)

17:31.150 --> 17:33.617
<i> The spell said when his name</i>
<i> was nothing but ash,</i>

17:33.686 --> 17:36.320
<i> I'd be free of him.</i>

17:38.724 --> 17:40.224
(flames roar)

17:41.294 --> 17:45.696
♪♪♪

17:45.698 --> 17:47.432
(flames roar)

17:47.567 --> 17:49.333
<i> (deep exhale)</i>

17:52.905 --> 17:54.305
- (jenny clears her throat)

17:55.909 --> 17:58.775
- The ritual cleansed
my attachment to him.

17:58.812 --> 18:01.779
For the first time
in my repressed,

18:01.914 --> 18:04.649
Catholic life, I felt free.

18:08.788 --> 18:10.787
Um...

18:10.824 --> 18:13.791
I'm happy to talk to you
more about andy,

18:13.926 --> 18:15.792
But can we do it at my shop?

18:15.829 --> 18:18.795
I need to recharge
with my crystals.

18:21.267 --> 18:23.468
- She said mine's for peace
of mind.

18:23.603 --> 18:25.536
What's yours?
- Healing.

18:26.739 --> 18:28.539
- Is it weird that
we took presents

18:28.674 --> 18:30.875
From a potential murderer?
- No.

18:32.745 --> 18:34.946
- You bought stuff from her.

18:35.081 --> 18:36.947
- A friend's birthday's
coming, up,

18:36.983 --> 18:38.882
So she's into all this stuff.
- Okay.

18:39.986 --> 18:41.618
You know what else is weird?

18:41.654 --> 18:44.555
Why would a self-described
repressed catholic girl

18:44.624 --> 18:46.691
Go looking for an occult spell,

18:46.826 --> 18:49.694
And then,
perform it in the woods,

18:49.829 --> 18:52.829
In the middle of the night,
alone?

18:52.866 --> 18:54.632
- Maybe she got tired
of praying.

18:54.634 --> 18:56.234
(jenny's phone rings)

18:56.369 --> 18:58.569
- Oh, hey.
Hey, river.

18:58.704 --> 19:01.138
<i> River: What does this</i>
<i> look like, to you?</i>

19:01.273 --> 19:03.574
- Well, that looks like
a blurry foot.

19:03.709 --> 19:04.909
- (exhales)

19:04.978 --> 19:07.511
Doctor garcia,
could you zoom out, please?

19:07.514 --> 19:09.113
- Yeah.

19:09.248 --> 19:11.248
Thanks for letting me
take the lead

19:11.284 --> 19:14.118
On this autopsy, doctor cooper.
It's a dream come true.

19:14.253 --> 19:16.787
- Of course. It actually
worked out perfectly

19:16.789 --> 19:19.456
Because doctor lum-davis
has food poisoning, so...

19:19.492 --> 19:21.525
- (small chuckle)
- uh-huh.

19:21.528 --> 19:23.727
- Show her.
- Oh, right.

19:24.998 --> 19:27.331
River: (sighs) see these teeny,
tiny puncture wounds?

19:27.367 --> 19:29.433
- Yeah, I see them.

19:30.637 --> 19:32.203
- He's got them on both feet.

19:32.205 --> 19:34.171
- Any idea what caused them?

19:34.306 --> 19:35.973
- Well...

19:37.343 --> 19:44.348
♪♪♪

19:44.350 --> 19:47.084
♪♪♪

19:47.153 --> 19:48.552
This.

19:48.555 --> 19:50.487
- That looks like the end
of a thumbtack.

19:50.557 --> 19:53.223
- We'll call you back if we
find anything else super weird.

19:54.327 --> 19:56.694
<i> - Great. Thanks, river.</i>

19:56.829 --> 19:58.696
I've read about case studies

19:58.698 --> 20:00.698
Where the decedent had these
kinds of injuries before.

20:00.700 --> 20:02.300
- And what were the findings?

20:02.435 --> 20:04.768
- They were all victims
of torture.

20:09.442 --> 20:11.909
Ubdue andy,

20:11.911 --> 20:13.444
To torture him.

20:13.513 --> 20:15.512
- Maybe she drugged him
and tied him up.

20:15.548 --> 20:17.782
- No, there's no ligature marks
and the tox screen

20:17.784 --> 20:20.651
Came back negative for
tranquilizers and narcotics.

20:20.653 --> 20:22.185
- What about alcohol?

20:22.222 --> 20:24.322
- Hm, there was enough in his
system to get him buzzed,

20:24.457 --> 20:27.191
But not enough
to knock him out.

20:27.193 --> 20:28.526
- An accomplice, then?

20:28.661 --> 20:30.328
(jenny's phone rings)
- maybe.

20:30.330 --> 20:32.263
Oh, hey, I gotta get this.
- All right.

20:32.332 --> 20:34.364
- I'll meet you outside.

20:34.400 --> 20:36.066
- Hey, river, give me a sec.

20:36.068 --> 20:37.835
- G-good, goodbye.

20:39.973 --> 20:41.539
- Goodbye.

20:41.541 --> 20:46.143
♪♪♪

20:46.145 --> 20:47.678
(door opens and closes)

20:50.383 --> 20:52.549
- Hey, river. How's it goin'?

20:52.585 --> 20:54.651
Slow but doctor garcia is good.

20:55.888 --> 20:58.022
- Well, that's good to know.
You find anything else?

20:58.091 --> 20:59.824
- There is something
with the heart.

20:59.826 --> 21:03.627
There is a microscopic hole
between the upper chambers.

21:03.696 --> 21:06.764
- Like an atrial septal defect?
- Exactly.

21:06.766 --> 21:09.500
It's too insignificant
to kill him,

21:09.502 --> 21:12.737
But it is interesting.
- Huh.

21:12.872 --> 21:15.339
- We're examining
respiratory tree.

21:15.375 --> 21:17.808
If you'd like to observe,
doctor cooper?

21:20.647 --> 21:23.881
(exhales)
just give me a second.

21:25.485 --> 21:29.653
♪♪♪

21:29.689 --> 21:31.722
(scissors snap)

21:37.430 --> 21:39.963
(wet squishy sound)

21:41.067 --> 21:43.000
- Well, that's interesting.

21:43.002 --> 21:44.735
(wet squishy sound)

21:51.678 --> 21:54.111
- 34-year-old congealed blood.

21:54.147 --> 21:56.514
Perfectly preserved.

21:56.649 --> 21:58.382
- That blood is as old as me.

21:58.518 --> 22:00.150
Both: (chuckle)

22:01.321 --> 22:03.220
- Uh, thank you, dennis,
for all your good work.

22:04.290 --> 22:05.890
Thanks, guys.

22:05.892 --> 22:10.127
♪♪♪

22:10.262 --> 22:12.629
- Ah. Sorry.

22:14.033 --> 22:16.133
Sometimes I get so excited
about my work

22:16.268 --> 22:19.103
I forget that I've gotta
be careful with my hand.

22:19.105 --> 22:21.305
- There's no need to apologize.

22:21.307 --> 22:23.974
Your hand seems steady
enough to me.

22:25.211 --> 22:27.511
- (sighs)

22:28.647 --> 22:30.581
River,

22:30.583 --> 22:33.184
Would you like to grab
a drink sometime

22:33.186 --> 22:35.852
When we're uh,
no longer colleagues?

22:38.057 --> 22:40.524
♪♪♪

22:40.526 --> 22:43.693
- I would love to grab a drink
with you, doctor garcia.

22:46.466 --> 22:48.132
- Great. Great.

22:48.267 --> 22:51.268
Uh, martinis, it is!

22:51.404 --> 22:52.803
(both chuckle nervously)

22:52.938 --> 22:55.272
(grass crunches underfoot)

22:55.274 --> 22:57.074
(birds chirping)

22:57.143 --> 22:59.610
(ethereal music plays)

23:02.348 --> 23:05.149
- Andy had a hole in his heart.

23:05.218 --> 23:07.751
Dennis has a defect in his hand.

23:07.754 --> 23:09.486
- (grunts)

23:09.555 --> 23:11.955
- You wanna know
what I think this is?

23:14.760 --> 23:16.693
You do yoga?

23:16.695 --> 23:18.896
- Which question do you
want me to answer first?

23:18.965 --> 23:20.631
- Sorry, right.

23:20.766 --> 23:24.768
Um, I think both andy and
dennis have holt-oram syndrome.

23:26.038 --> 23:27.104
- Is that good or bad?

23:27.173 --> 23:28.906
- Holt-oram is a,
a genetic defect

23:28.975 --> 23:31.708
That's passed down
from parent to child.

23:33.312 --> 23:36.046
- Andy nyland went missing
34-years-ago.

23:36.182 --> 23:37.915
Let me guess how old dennis is.

23:37.984 --> 23:39.783
- He's 34.

23:39.786 --> 23:42.319
<i> (camera clicks)</i>
<i> man: Yeah, I got it here.</i>

23:42.455 --> 23:44.855
Angela: (sighs)
I don't know what to say.

23:44.857 --> 23:47.023
No one's ever put it
together before.

23:48.194 --> 23:49.927
(police radio chatter)

23:49.929 --> 23:51.795
I'll tell you what I remember,

23:51.864 --> 23:54.131
If you let me tell dennis
the truth.

23:55.868 --> 23:57.201
- Okay.

23:58.737 --> 24:00.737
- Angela, were you there
the night andy disappeared?

24:00.807 --> 24:03.140
(police radio chatter)

24:04.310 --> 24:06.143
- Helen and I were best friends,

24:06.212 --> 24:09.412
Which is why andy came to me
when things got bad with them.

24:09.449 --> 24:11.682
It started out with me
helping him.

24:11.817 --> 24:13.517
We got close,

24:13.653 --> 24:15.953
And then I broke
the cardinal rule.

24:15.955 --> 24:20.590
♪♪♪

24:23.996 --> 24:25.696
(fire crackles)

24:25.765 --> 24:32.102
♪♪♪

24:32.104 --> 24:34.371
(fire crackles)

24:37.477 --> 24:39.943
(paper crinkles)

24:41.347 --> 24:43.113
(footsteps crunch
in the foliage)

24:46.319 --> 24:48.785
(footsteps approach)

24:48.821 --> 24:50.588
- Ah!
- (screams)

24:50.590 --> 24:53.089
- (laughs) hey, it's me.

24:55.194 --> 24:57.194
(chuckles)

24:57.196 --> 24:59.730
<i> I'd let it slip,</i>
<i> about the ritual.</i>

24:59.865 --> 25:02.232
He thought it would be funny
to sneak up on helen and me.

25:03.603 --> 25:06.002
But I had something else
to tell him that night.

25:07.406 --> 25:09.005
I told him about the baby.

25:10.243 --> 25:12.076
He lost it.

25:12.078 --> 25:13.811
Said he'd skip town
if I kept it.

25:15.748 --> 25:17.548
I wanted to humiliate him.

25:19.018 --> 25:21.885
<i> Make him feel like I did</i>
<i> in that moment.</i>

25:21.954 --> 25:24.888
<i> So, I suggested we have sex</i>
<i> one last time.</i>

25:26.025 --> 25:28.091
<i> Like a send-off.</i>

25:28.160 --> 25:30.094
(belt buckle jingles)

25:34.267 --> 25:37.233
<i> When his clothes were off,</i>
<i> I told him to close his eyes,</i>

25:37.270 --> 25:39.336
<i> That I had a surprise for him.</i>

25:40.873 --> 25:42.739
<i> Then I took his clothes,</i>
<i> and I left.</i>

25:43.842 --> 25:46.176
<i> That was the last I saw andy.</i>

25:47.513 --> 25:49.379
I wish I could say I could
take it all back,

25:49.448 --> 25:50.981
But then,

25:51.050 --> 25:52.849
I wouldn't have dennis.

25:57.790 --> 25:59.590
(door slams)

25:59.659 --> 26:01.792
- (tired exhale)
(keys drop to ground)

26:01.794 --> 26:04.328
(donovan sighs)
(jenny grunts)

26:04.330 --> 26:06.196
- You gonna be okay to make it
back to the city?

26:06.332 --> 26:08.332
(exhales)
- one of the many, many perks

26:08.401 --> 26:10.601
Of quitting coffee.
Oh, jesus.

26:10.736 --> 26:12.536
- (chuckles)

26:12.538 --> 26:14.338
Oh, place is a little creepy,

26:14.340 --> 26:16.607
But roxanna did offer
to let us stay over.

26:16.742 --> 26:18.342
(dog barks in distance)

26:19.445 --> 26:21.144
- I mean, I'll stay,
if you stay.

26:22.281 --> 26:24.014
I have a gym bag in the car.

26:24.016 --> 26:26.150
- Well, that makes one of us.

26:26.285 --> 26:28.085
(hand taps lightly on chest)

26:28.154 --> 26:29.986
- Sleepover!
- (chuckles)

26:35.962 --> 26:37.527
(sips wine)

26:42.034 --> 26:43.767
(hushed) andy nyland...

26:44.837 --> 26:46.770
(phone rings)

26:47.906 --> 26:49.606
- Hi, jenny.

26:49.609 --> 26:51.941
- Hi. I just got
garcia's report.

26:53.045 --> 26:54.978
- The cause of death
was asphyxiation?

26:54.981 --> 26:57.814
- Not the best way to go -
suffocating on your own blood.

26:58.951 --> 27:00.451
- Oh, uh,

27:00.453 --> 27:03.721
Dennis found some
microscopic pink quartz,

27:03.723 --> 27:06.823
Feldspar, and mica
embedded in the mask.

27:06.859 --> 27:08.659
- Those elements make granite.

27:08.728 --> 27:10.927
- He was struck in the face
with a rock?

27:10.929 --> 27:12.996
- That's right!
- Well, that's it.

27:12.999 --> 27:14.665
<i> Have a, have a good night,</i>
<i> okay?</i>

27:14.734 --> 27:16.667
- We will.

27:16.802 --> 27:19.670
(footsteps thud, door opens)

27:23.142 --> 27:26.810
♪♪♪

27:26.879 --> 27:29.012
- (sighs)

27:34.220 --> 27:36.052
(knock on door)

27:38.758 --> 27:42.092
(sheets rustle)

27:42.161 --> 27:44.094
(ominous music)

27:44.096 --> 27:46.062
(door creaks open)

27:47.633 --> 27:49.566
- Helen? Sorry, um--

27:50.636 --> 27:53.303
- Are you more of a water
person

27:53.305 --> 27:55.105
Or a fire person?

27:56.575 --> 27:57.841
- Um, I don't,
I don't know, but--

27:57.877 --> 28:00.276
- When we met,
and I took your hand,

28:01.347 --> 28:03.247
I got your psychic energy on me,

28:03.249 --> 28:05.649
And I haven't been able
to get it off.

28:05.651 --> 28:07.985
You're in a dark place,
doctor cooper,

28:08.120 --> 28:09.920
And I'd like to try to help you.

28:12.992 --> 28:15.091
(fire crackles gently)

28:16.662 --> 28:18.328
(ominous music)

28:18.464 --> 28:24.668
♪♪♪

28:24.670 --> 28:26.770
Helen: I see you,
jenny cooper,

28:27.807 --> 28:30.774
The parts of you
that even you can't see.

28:33.479 --> 28:37.547
And I'm asking you
to let me help you.

28:40.820 --> 28:43.487
- Help you what?

28:43.556 --> 28:46.623
- Imagine the thing
that has a hold on you.

28:46.692 --> 28:48.959
<i> Jenny: (reluctant exhale)</i>

28:48.961 --> 28:51.027
- Someone from your past.

28:53.699 --> 28:56.866
And then imagine being free
of the weight of it.

29:00.439 --> 29:03.373
(crystals clink lightly)

29:05.177 --> 29:07.044
(fire crackles)

29:07.179 --> 29:14.651
♪♪♪

29:14.653 --> 29:16.987
- Yeah, um...

29:17.056 --> 29:19.589
(sage hisses)

29:22.595 --> 29:23.893
- Unclench your heart.

29:25.330 --> 29:27.263
Unlock your mind.

29:27.299 --> 29:30.300
<i> Past and present now aligned.</i>

29:31.971 --> 29:35.505
♪♪♪

29:39.478 --> 29:41.211
(rock clinks gently)

29:41.346 --> 29:43.013
♪♪♪

29:43.015 --> 29:45.349
- Close your eyes.

29:45.484 --> 29:46.850
(sage crackles)

29:47.887 --> 29:53.156
♪♪♪

29:53.159 --> 29:55.225
Let go.

29:57.897 --> 30:00.063
(gasps, music stops abruptly)

30:03.369 --> 30:05.535
(ominous music)

30:07.640 --> 30:14.578
♪♪♪

30:24.490 --> 30:26.123
Uds on ground)

30:26.258 --> 30:28.024
(hard exhales)

30:31.997 --> 30:33.630
- Why do I get the feeling

30:33.699 --> 30:36.400
I'm in a rocky training montage
all of a sudden?

30:36.402 --> 30:38.201
- Found it under my bed.

30:38.270 --> 30:40.136
(pants)

30:40.172 --> 30:42.139
Okay, so,

30:42.141 --> 30:44.140
Here's what I'm thinking, right.

30:44.176 --> 30:46.743
Andy finds out that helen
and angela

30:46.745 --> 30:49.479
Are doing this cleansing spell

30:49.548 --> 30:52.482
And he goes to the woods,
puts on a mask to scare them.

30:52.551 --> 30:55.752
Angela tells him about the baby,
she steals his clothes,

30:55.754 --> 30:58.622
He makes his way back
to the fire, right,

30:58.691 --> 31:00.957
Which is where someone

31:01.026 --> 31:03.026
Hits him in the face
with a rock.

31:03.028 --> 31:05.695
Now, he stumbles
on the witch's bottle,

31:05.731 --> 31:08.765
Which is how he gets the tacks
in the bottom of his feet.

31:08.900 --> 31:10.667
So, either angela's lying

31:10.802 --> 31:12.936
Or helen is,

31:12.972 --> 31:14.771
Or I mean, I guess...

31:14.840 --> 31:16.640
I mean, both could be lying,

31:16.709 --> 31:18.308
I just, I don't know.
I'm not sure.

31:18.377 --> 31:20.243
What do you think?

31:21.380 --> 31:23.579
- I think we should sleep on it,
rock-o.

31:23.616 --> 31:25.248
Get back in the ring
in the morning.

31:25.317 --> 31:27.317
- (sighs) I'm good.

31:27.319 --> 31:29.852
- Yeah, but maybe
I'm scared of the dark.

31:31.857 --> 31:33.523
- (sighs, sniffles)

31:34.860 --> 31:37.060
Fine, let's go.

31:37.096 --> 31:39.262
- Apollo creed wins again!
(pretend crowd cheer)

31:40.866 --> 31:42.532
(zipper rasps)

31:42.568 --> 31:44.401
(knock on door)

31:46.405 --> 31:48.571
(footsteps thud, door opens)

31:51.677 --> 31:53.743
- Morning.
- Hey, morning.

31:53.779 --> 31:55.479
- Hey, got you a tea.

31:55.614 --> 31:57.814
- Thank you.
- Now, check this out.

31:57.950 --> 32:00.350
- Sorry, is this uh,
the witchcraft book

32:00.352 --> 32:02.285
That you bought
for your friend?

32:02.354 --> 32:04.554
- Well, first off, I'd make
a kick-ass warlock.

32:04.556 --> 32:07.958
Secondly, I like anything
that helps me solve a murder.

32:08.093 --> 32:10.027
All right, now helen said
she cast a spell

32:10.029 --> 32:11.962
To rid someone from her life.
- Mm-hmm.

32:12.031 --> 32:14.230
- Now, according to my
research--

32:14.266 --> 32:16.632
- So, your,
your warlock research?

32:16.669 --> 32:18.769
No, please, tell me.
Tell me all about...

32:18.771 --> 32:20.437
- Yeah, according
to my research.

32:20.439 --> 32:22.605
- ...Your research. Yep, mhm.
- The triangle of solomon

32:22.641 --> 32:25.175
Does just that.
It requires three stones -

32:25.310 --> 32:27.778
Rose quartz, amethyst,
and granite.

32:27.780 --> 32:30.047
Each wielded by
a separate witch.

32:31.650 --> 32:33.850
- But that's,
that three witches.

32:35.287 --> 32:37.053
- Yeah.

32:37.122 --> 32:38.922
- We only have two.

32:39.057 --> 32:40.724
(book thuds shut)

32:40.859 --> 32:42.892
- Wait.

32:45.197 --> 32:47.597
(door closes, door opens)

32:47.666 --> 32:49.932
I remember seeing something.

32:52.171 --> 32:54.904
(pages rustle)

32:57.276 --> 32:59.009
Best friends.

32:59.011 --> 33:01.677
- Helen, angela, and--
- yeah.

33:03.348 --> 33:05.015
Yeah.
(book thuds shut)

33:06.819 --> 33:08.718
(door creaks open)

33:14.226 --> 33:16.426
(cap rattles, vodka burbles)

33:23.702 --> 33:25.235
(bottle clangs)

33:27.906 --> 33:29.839
- Don't sneak up on me,
like that. (chuckles)

33:36.715 --> 33:38.782
- Roxanna, were you there
that night?

33:38.917 --> 33:40.850
- Uh, I'm way too hangover
to know

33:40.919 --> 33:42.652
What you're talkin' about.

33:42.788 --> 33:45.321
- Helen and angela,
they told us the whole story.

33:45.391 --> 33:47.090
- Uh, I don't believe them.

33:48.160 --> 33:50.093
We made a vow never
to talk about that.

33:53.332 --> 33:54.864
Oh, I see.

33:55.934 --> 33:58.335
Clever, detective mcavoy.

33:58.337 --> 34:00.603
- They didn't name you,
but they both told us

34:00.672 --> 34:02.205
Their version of what
happened that night.

34:03.475 --> 34:05.042
Maybe you'd like
to tell us yours?

34:08.213 --> 34:10.280
(gulps)

34:13.685 --> 34:15.352
(exhales)

34:15.354 --> 34:17.153
(fire crackles)

34:20.292 --> 34:22.692
<i> Andy could be sweet</i>
<i> and sensitive,</i>

34:22.761 --> 34:24.861
<i> But he was also a horny</i>
<i> teenaged boy.</i>

34:26.398 --> 34:28.065
<i> And helen wanted to wait.</i>

34:29.701 --> 34:32.102
<i>By then, I'd figured out he was</i>
<i> screwing around with angela.</i>

34:33.438 --> 34:35.372
<i> So, I decided enough</i>
<i> was enough.</i>

34:35.507 --> 34:37.140
(fire crackles)

34:39.244 --> 34:41.311
This will help you loosen up

34:41.313 --> 34:43.246
And tap into the magic.

34:44.382 --> 34:46.116
- I don't think so.

34:46.251 --> 34:48.518
- Okay, you know I'd never do
anything to hurt you, right?

34:48.587 --> 34:50.286
I just want you
to be free of him.

34:52.657 --> 34:55.024
- Yes! And some for me.

34:56.728 --> 34:58.161
(plastic crinkles)

35:00.332 --> 35:01.998
(ominous music)

35:02.067 --> 35:06.937
♪♪♪

35:06.939 --> 35:08.939
(excited squeal)
here we go! (chuckles)

35:10.809 --> 35:16.146
♪♪♪

35:17.382 --> 35:21.884
(fire crackles)

35:21.920 --> 35:24.287
(paper rustles)

35:28.861 --> 35:30.626
(items clink in glass)

35:31.763 --> 35:33.763
(sizzling)

35:35.968 --> 35:37.367
After it was all over,

35:37.436 --> 35:39.369
Helen said that she felt good.

35:40.506 --> 35:42.372
You know, that she,
that she felt free.

35:44.843 --> 35:47.777
I said I'd walk her home,
while angela peed.

35:49.114 --> 35:50.447
<i> Halfway to her house,</i>

35:50.582 --> 35:52.982
Helen remembered she left
her notebook behind,

35:53.018 --> 35:55.252
And she was freaking out

35:55.254 --> 35:56.986
That someone would find it

35:57.022 --> 35:59.723
<i> And tell her parents that</i>
<i> she'd been doing witchcraft,</i>

35:59.858 --> 36:02.726
So I said I'd go back,
I'd go back and get it.

36:04.897 --> 36:06.329
(footstep crunch
in the foliage)

36:06.398 --> 36:08.097
(giggles)

36:10.702 --> 36:12.602
(jar clinks)

36:12.604 --> 36:13.870
(suspenseful music)

36:13.939 --> 36:16.239
(growls)
(screams, glass shatters)

36:17.676 --> 36:20.076
(thudding blow,
falls heavily to ground)

36:20.078 --> 36:22.111
(panicked breathing)
oh god!

36:28.620 --> 36:31.254
I know I was high,
but I swear to you,

36:34.960 --> 36:36.960
That wolf was real.

36:39.364 --> 36:45.835
♪♪♪

36:45.971 --> 36:47.336
- (sighs)

36:49.041 --> 36:51.040
<i> Roxanna...</i>

36:53.545 --> 36:55.278
- Whatever it is, just say it.

37:01.954 --> 37:03.320
- When we found andy's body,

37:06.992 --> 37:08.858
He was wearing a wolf mask.

37:10.128 --> 37:11.827
- No, he, that ca--

37:19.004 --> 37:21.537
Oh, no, no, no, no, no, no.

37:21.607 --> 37:23.273
(breathes shakily)

37:28.347 --> 37:30.480
I did it. I killed him.

37:32.985 --> 37:34.551
I killed my brother?

37:36.355 --> 37:38.621
(gasps) I killed my brother.
I killed andy?

37:38.624 --> 37:40.890
(crying)
oh, god! Andy!

37:43.028 --> 37:45.161
<i> (sobs) I killed andy!</i>
<i> Oh, god!</i>

37:46.765 --> 37:48.431
<i> (sobbing)</i>

37:55.173 --> 37:57.974
- This was all just
a horrible mistake.

38:00.112 --> 38:01.444
- I don't see anyone
prosecuting roxanna

38:01.579 --> 38:03.279
Under these circumstances.

38:05.851 --> 38:07.784
But we still don't know
how andy got into the bog.

38:08.854 --> 38:10.619
(donovan's phone rings)

38:13.792 --> 38:15.858
I hate loose ends.
- Yeah.

38:15.927 --> 38:17.994
- Sorry, I gotta take this.
- Mm-hmm.

38:22.100 --> 38:23.933
- Goodbye!
- Bye. Hello?

38:23.935 --> 38:25.802
(door opens and closes)

38:31.643 --> 38:33.609
(pencil rasps on paper)

38:36.348 --> 38:37.947
(footsteps approach)

38:41.353 --> 38:42.885
- Goodbye.

38:45.223 --> 38:47.456
Everyday, goodbye.

38:50.628 --> 38:52.461
(footsteps thud)

38:55.500 --> 38:57.466
(crying)

38:58.770 --> 39:00.970
- Mr. Nyland,

39:01.106 --> 39:03.205
Did you see andy the night
he disappeared?

39:05.009 --> 39:07.810
- (sobs) good boy.

39:09.981 --> 39:11.648
(crying)

39:16.321 --> 39:18.354
- You buried one child
to save another.

39:22.394 --> 39:23.692
- So, I,

39:25.731 --> 39:28.264
I... Am...

39:29.401 --> 39:31.301
I am so sad.

39:31.436 --> 39:32.902
(footsteps approach)

39:34.539 --> 39:36.406
- What are you talking
to my father about--?

39:36.408 --> 39:37.874
Get away from him!

39:37.943 --> 39:39.743
He doesn't have to know, okay?

39:39.878 --> 39:41.510
He, he's been through enough.

39:42.781 --> 39:44.681
You don't understand.

39:47.018 --> 39:49.619
- I do.
More than I can explain,

39:49.688 --> 39:51.520
And you don't wanna go
through this alone.

39:52.824 --> 39:54.824
<i> (door opens)</i>

39:54.893 --> 39:56.525
Not again.
(door closes)

40:01.699 --> 40:03.532
- Did you call them?

40:04.569 --> 40:07.870
- No.
They just knew to come.

40:11.376 --> 40:12.709
- I don't understand.

40:12.711 --> 40:14.177
I, I thought the radiation
was supposed to help?

40:14.179 --> 40:15.311
<i> Dr. Cheng: It has helped.</i>

40:15.313 --> 40:16.979
<i> Your tumour has shrunk</i>
<i> considerably.</i>

40:17.015 --> 40:19.249
- Okay, but,
but now you're telling me

40:19.251 --> 40:21.184
I have a hole in my spine.

40:22.387 --> 40:23.986
How, how big a hole
are we talkin'?

40:24.022 --> 40:26.256
Are we talkin' pinhead size,
dime size?

40:26.391 --> 40:28.057
Hell, a golf ball size?

40:28.193 --> 40:30.326
<i> - I'd like you to come in</i>
<i> so we can talk about this.</i>

40:30.328 --> 40:31.928
<i> I know you're very busy,</i>

40:31.930 --> 40:33.797
<i>But this is something we should</i>
<i> talk about in person.</i>

40:35.000 --> 40:36.599
- What's the worst-case
scenario?

40:36.601 --> 40:38.401
<i> - Why don't I start</i>
<i> with the good news?</i>

40:38.536 --> 40:40.003
<i> It's completely operable.</i>

40:40.005 --> 40:41.637
- That's not what I asked you.

40:42.707 --> 40:45.275
<i> - Okay, well,</i>
<i> there is a small chance,</i>

40:45.410 --> 40:46.743
<i> However, if we operate,</i>

40:46.878 --> 40:49.078
<i> That it could affect</i>
<i> your ability to walk.</i>

40:50.949 --> 40:52.415
<i> (crow caws)</i>

40:53.819 --> 40:56.085
(footsteps approach lightly)

40:56.154 --> 40:57.753
- Hey.
- Hey.

40:59.891 --> 41:02.292
Tell me you have what we need,
and we can go home.

41:03.962 --> 41:05.762
- Yeah, I'm uh,

41:05.897 --> 41:08.163
I'm gonna rule andy's death
an accident.

41:09.367 --> 41:11.367
I feel like this family
could use some peace.

41:11.436 --> 41:13.536
(door shuts)
- peace. Mm-hmm.

41:15.207 --> 41:16.639
I like the sound of that.

41:18.844 --> 41:24.647
♪♪♪

